# ARCHON Homelab

Segmented enterprise-style homelab built to simulate network security operations, monitoring, logging, and infrastructure management.

## Overview

This project documents the design and buildout of a cybersecurity-focused homelab intended to emulate core enterprise components and security functions. The environment is being developed to support hands-on practice with segmentation, monitoring, detection, logging, system administration, and defensive operations.

## Topology

![Network Topology](topology/network-topology.png)

## Core Components

Firewall - Enforces traffic control, segmentation, and policy inspection  
SIEM - Centralizes logs for visibility, analysis, and detection  
Domain Controller - Supports authentication, identity, and centralized policy management  
Raspberry Pi Monitor - Provides lightweight health monitoring and supporting services  
NAS - Stores backups, logs, and supporting lab data  
UPS - Maintains short-term power continuity and protects infrastructure stability  
Virtual Machines - Simulate user, server, and attacker systems for testing and validation

## Objectives

- Build and document a segmented homelab environment
- Practice network defense and monitoring workflows
- Simulate enterprise infrastructure and security operations
- Create a public portfolio of hands-on cybersecurity work

